Date: 1994-12-16

Title: Homological Algebra and Yang-Mills Theory

Comments: 20 pages in LaTeX

Journal-ref: J.Pure Appl.Algebra 100 (1995) 3-18

The antifield-BRST formalism and the various cohomologies associated with itare surveyed and illustrated in the context of Yang-Mills gauge theory. Inparticular, the central role played by the Koszul-Tate resolution and itsrelation to the characteristic cohomology are stressed.